1)Add .cshtml file.
2)Include jquery path and js file path.
<!-- include jQuery first -->
<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js"></script>

<!-- then your page script -->
<script src="~/JqueryScripts/Grid.js"></script>

3)in the js file add document.ready function
4) Add js file reference path above document.ready function.
/// <reference path="../scripts/jquery-3.7.0.js" />

5)In the controller action method, for the parameter values to match the exact model values, use same property name in js file
  var input = {
   // keys match Employee property names in DomainEntity\Employee.cs
      Name: txtname,
      Email: txtemail,
      Salary: txtsalary,
      Comments: txtcomments
  }

6)Use get and post methods in controller.


